# HTML `Notes`

### What is _Html_?

> <u>Ans</u> :- <lable style="color:green">**HTML**</lable> Stands for<lable style="color:yellow"> _Hyper Text Markup Language_ for crate web page.</lable> <span style="color: Lime;">Hypertext defines the link between the web pages. The markup language is used to define the text document within the tag which defines the structure of web pages. HTML 5 is the fifth and current version of HTML. It has improved the markup available for documents and has introduced application programming interfaces (API) and Document Object Model (DOM).</span>

### What is `Elements`?

> <u>Ans</u> :- An **HTML** elements is components of the **HTML** _DOC_ that tells a browser how to structure and interpret a part of the document.

### What is sementic and non-sementic tag?

> <u>Ans</u> :- Semantic HTML tags convey the meaning of the content they contain, while non-semantic HTML tags are used for formatting or layout.

- sementic_tag :- `<footer>, <artical>, <nav>`
- non-sementic_tag :- `<span>, <div>`

<img style="position:relative ; left:50% ; width:70%" src="https://techgurudehradun.in/blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/html-semantic-layout.jpg" alt="sementic&non-sementic_tag"/>

### What is Attributes?

> <u>Ans</u> :- An **HTML** attribute is _a word or set of words that provide additional information about an **HTML** element. Attributes are placed inside the opening tag of an **HTML** element. They can be used to change the appearance or behavior of an element_.

<img style="position:relative ; left:50% ; width:70%" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="attributes"/>

### What is Formate?

> <u>Ans</u>
>
> - Markup language: HTML uses tags (like `<p>` for paragraph, `<h1>` for heading) to define different elements within a document.
> - File extension: HTML files are usually identified by the ".html" extension.
> - Basic structure: An HTML document typically includes a `<head>` section for metadata (like page title) and a `<body>` section containing the visible content on the webpage.

<img style="position:relative ; left:50% ; width:70%" src="https://media.geeksforgeeks.org/wp-content/cdn-uploads/20220401160946/HTML-Basic-Format-768x534.png"  alt="format"/>

### What is Tags?

> <u>Ans</u> HTML tags Define the structure and content of an HTML document, Determine the type of element represented, Enclose content, and Turn formatting features on and off.

| _`Tag`_           |     | _`Discription`_                                           |
| ----------------- | --- | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| _**`<html>`**_    |     | The root element                                          |
| _**`<head> `**_   |     | The document head                                         |
| _**`<title>`**_   |     | The page title                                            |
| _**`<body>`**_    |     | The page's content                                        |
| _**`<h1>`**_      |     | A section heading                                         |
| _**`<p>`**_       |     | A paragraph                                               |
| _**`<a>`**_       |     | A link                                                    |
| _**`<img>`**_     |     | An image                                                  |
| _**`<abbr>`**_    |     | An abbreviation or acronym                                |
| _**`<address>`**_ |     | Contact information for the author or owner of a document |
| _**`<div>`**_     |     | A division or container                                   |
